    "intro": "Interpretation moves from what the text says to what it means — tracking the author's theological intent within the double context of Zechariah's post-exilic moment and the canonical arc that runs from Sinai to Revelation. The movements below follow the chapter's three natural divisions: the vision (2:1-5), the oracle (2:6-12), and the doxological close (2:13). Greek and Hebrew notes supplement where the original language sharpens what English flattens.",
